# Semantic Library Search

An AI-powered library search tool that finds books by meaning, not just keywords. Built with sentence transformers, FAISS vector search, and Claude.

## Demo

🤗 [Live on HuggingFace Spaces](https://huggingface.co/spaces/AngelaColmen/semantic-library-search)

## How It Works

Traditional keyword search looks for exact word matches. Semantic search understands the *meaning* behind a query — so searching for "stories about survival against the odds" will surface books that match that theme even if those exact words never appear in the title or description.

Under the hood:
1. Each book in the catalog is converted into a vector (a list of numbers representing its meaning) using a sentence transformer model
2. When you search, your query is converted into a vector the same way
3. FAISS finds the books whose vectors are closest to your query vector
4. Optionally, Claude explains in plain language why those books match your search

## Features

- Semantic search across a 200-book catalog spanning fiction, science, history, social justice, technology, philosophy, psychology, and library science
- Adjustable number of results (1–5)
- Optional AI-powered explanations of why each result matched, powered by Claude
- Example searches to get started

## How to Use

1. Visit the [live demo](https://huggingface.co/spaces/AngelaColmen/semantic-library-search)
2. Type a search query in plain language — no need for exact titles or keywords
3. Optionally paste your [Anthropic API key](https://console.anthropic.com) to enable AI explanations
4. Click **Search**

## Example Searches

```
books about artificial intelligence and society
stories about race and justice in America
women who made a difference in science
how governments control people
climate change and the future of the planet
libraries and the organization of knowledge
```

## Tech Stack

- [Sentence Transformers](https://www.sbert.net/) — converts text into semantic vectors using the `all-MiniLM-L6-v2` model
- [FAISS](https://github.com/facebookresearch/faiss) — fast vector similarity search by Meta
- [Gradio](https://gradio.app/) — web interface
- [Claude](https://anthropic.com) (claude-sonnet-4) — optional AI explanations via the Anthropic API
- Python, pandas, numpy

## Setup for Local Development

**1. Clone the repo**
```bash
git clone https://github.com/angelacolmen/semantic-library-search
cd semantic-library-search
```

**2. Create a virtual environment**
```bash
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate  # Windows
```

**3. Install dependencies**
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

**4. Build the search index**
```bash
python build_index.py
```

**5. Run the app**
```bash
python app.py
```

Then open `http://127.0.0.1:7860` in your browser.

